Safety apps may help to increase your #safety when using devices like mobile phones, iPads and tablets. Each app has different information and services. See our website for a list of apps, including 1800RESPECT Sunny and Daisy apps.  https://t.co/8EPR8U9kEt

The #1800RESPECT Disability Support Toolkit it now online. It provides resources for frontline professionals supporting people with #disability who have been impacted by #sexualassault and #domesticviolence. The toolkit is available on our website. https://t.co/Fk4VcuwdOQ

If you are worried about unhealthy, abusive or #violent behaviour in any of your relationships, qualified counsellors, information and support are available 24 hours a day, every day of the year. You can call 1800 737 732 or visit https://t.co/FvWH1Y4R8z.

1800RESPECT is Australia‚Äôs national #sexualassault, family and #domesticviolence support service. Anyone can contact us 24/7 for information, counselling and referrals via phone or webchat. Phone 1800 737 732 or visit our website. https://t.co/bcJlxOb3Rv #1800respect

#Financialabuse can happen to anyone. You're not alone and #support is available. Start by visiting the #1800RESPECT Financial Abuse Support Toolkit for advice on first steps about housing support, legal assistance and financial management. https://t.co/HIyJctbVin

Our Easy English booklets explain what violence and abuse is, and how to get support. They have been developed with Women with Disabilities Australia, have been user group tested and are easy to use. Downloadable PDFs are available from our website. https://t.co/Fk4VcuwdOQ

1800RESPECT continues to operate during the COVID19 health emergency, available 24/7. Call 1800 737 732 via web chat on our website at https://t.co/FvWH1Y4R8z. If you are in immediate danger, call 000.  https://t.co/tB0rS7vR5L
